snippet.textDisplay:
Been watching Linus Tech Tips & TechLinked (or any other LMG channel), and they are all awesome.
Just a small suggestion (I beg you all), please start pronouncing "Tesla" with and S instead of an Z.

Nikola Tesla is, was and always will be one of the greatest scientists and inventor, and just to pay back some respect to that monumental man we should at least start pronouncing his last name correctly (with an S instead of an Z). I know Slavic languages aren't popular in the world, but every time I hear "TeZla" my ears start to bleed. 

The issue isn't just with people of Slavic origin, scientist from across the globe that devoted their entire lives to improve the world we live in get their first and last names neutered in their non-native languages.
Thanks!
